🚀 Michael Maxwell Mwasame - Portfolio Website [https://myportfolio-ecru-alpha.vercel.app/]

A modern, responsive full-stack developer portfolio showcasing my skills, projects, and professional journey. Built with vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript featuring dynamic content loading and smooth animations.

🌟 Features

- Dynamic Content Loading: Modular section-based architecture for optimal performance
- Responsive Design: Fully responsive across all devices and screen sizes
- Modern UI/UX: Clean, professional design with smooth animations and transitions
- Interactive Elements: Typing animations, carousel galleries, and hover effects
- Resume Download: Integrated PDF resume download functionality
- Contact Form: Functional contact form with validation
- Loading Screen: Elegant loading animation for better user experience
- Social Integration: Direct links to GitHub, LinkedIn, and contact information

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- Frontend: HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript (Vanilla)
- Icons: Font Awesome 6.0.0
- Deployment: Vercel
- Version Control: Git & GitHub

## 📁 Project Structure

```
portfolio/
├── index.html              # Main entry point
├── styles.css              # Global styles and animations
├── script.js               # Main JavaScript functionality
├── images/                 # Image assets
└── sections/              # Modular HTML sections
    ├── about.html         # About me section
    ├── skills.html        # Technical skills
    ├── experience.html    # Work experience
    ├── education.html     # Educational background
    ├── projects.html      # Portfolio projects
    ├── gallery.html       # Project gallery/carousel
    ├── community.html     # Community involvement
    ├── certifications.html # Certifications and achievements
    └── contact.html       # Contact form and information
```

## 🚀 Quick Start

### Prerequisites

- Web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
- Code editor (VS Code recommended)
- Git

### Installation

1. Clone the repository
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/maximasprim/PLP_PORTFOLIO.git
   cd portfolio
   ```

2. Open locally
   - Open `index.html` in your web browser, or
   - Use a local server (recommended):
   ```bash
   
   # Using VS Code Live Server extension
   Right-click index.html → "Open with Live Server"
   ```

3. View in browser
   ```
   http://127.0.0.1:5500/index.html
   ```

